usage: chemkit pka [-h] --ha HA --a-minus A_MINUS --method {xtb,mopac,dft,hf}
                   [--mode {absolute,reference}] [--solvent SOLVENT]
                   [--ha-charge HA_CHARGE] [--ha-mult HA_MULT]
                   [--a-minus-mult A_MINUS_MULT] [--temperature TEMPERATURE]
                   [--pressure PRESSURE]
                   [--hplus-reference {tissandier_1998,kelly_2006}]
                   [--ref-ha REF_HA] [--ref-a-minus REF_A_MINUS]
                   [--pka-ref PKA_REF] [--ref-ha-charge REF_HA_CHARGE]
                   [--ref-ha-mult REF_HA_MULT]
                   [--ref-a-minus-mult REF_A_MINUS_MULT]
                   [--tier {fast,standard,accurate}] [--functional FUNCTIONAL]
                   [--basis BASIS] [--density-fit] [--out OUT]
                   [--accept-defaults] [--stdout {json,path,none}]
                   [--allow-unconverged]

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --ha HA               xyz of the protonated form (HA).
  --a-minus A_MINUS     xyz of the deprotonated form (A⁻).
  --method {xtb,mopac,dft,hf}
                        Same method is applied to every species in the cycle.
  --mode {absolute,reference}
                        absolute: uses literature G(H+,aq). reference: uses a
                        known acid (--ref-ha, --ref-a-minus, --pka-ref).
                        Reference is far more accurate.
  --solvent SOLVENT     Implicit solvent (default 'water' — required for the
                        absolute G(H+) reference to apply).
  --ha-charge HA_CHARGE
                        Charge of HA (default 0). A⁻ charge is HA charge − 1.
  --ha-mult HA_MULT     HA multiplicity (default 1).
  --a-minus-mult A_MINUS_MULT
                        A⁻ multiplicity (default 1).
  --temperature TEMPERATURE
  --pressure PRESSURE
  --hplus-reference {tissandier_1998,kelly_2006}
                        Source for G(H+,aq). Tissandier −270.28 kcal/mol
                        (default); Kelly −265.9 kcal/mol shifts every pKa by
                        ~1.4 units.
  --ref-ha REF_HA       Reference acid HA xyz (reference mode).
  --ref-a-minus REF_A_MINUS
                        Reference base A⁻ xyz (reference mode).
  --pka-ref PKA_REF     Known experimental pKa of the reference acid
                        (reference mode).
  --ref-ha-charge REF_HA_CHARGE
  --ref-ha-mult REF_HA_MULT
  --ref-a-minus-mult REF_A_MINUS_MULT
  --tier {fast,standard,accurate}
  --functional FUNCTIONAL
  --basis BASIS
  --density-fit         Enable DFT/HF density fitting (RI). OFF by default
                        (exact integrals); opts into the ~3-10x SCF speedup.
  --out OUT
  --accept-defaults     Consent to silent DFT/HF defaults (tier=standard /
                        basis=def2-tzvp). Without it a DFT/HF run omitting
                        tier/functional/basis is refused. (pKa already pins
                        solvent=water.)
  --stdout {json,path,none}
                        What to print on stdout. 'json' = full result
                        (default), 'path' = compact one-line pointer to the
                        --out file plus convergence/warnings, 'none' = silent.
                        The --out JSON file is always written either way. Use
                        'path' to keep the full blob out of an agent's context
                        and read back fields with jq.
  --allow-unconverged, --no-gate
                        Downgrade the integrity hard-abort to a stamped
                        warning and exit 0 (result marked status=warning,
                        trustworthy=false, gate_bypassed=true). Use ONLY to
                        inspect a failed geometry (collapsed TS, non-converged
                        opt) — the headline number is NOT trustworthy.
